The paper presents a method for compressing deep convolutional neural networks for computer vision tasks, such as image classification and object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel weight sharing scheme using a 3D tensor, which falls under the scope of machine learning and neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves optimization techniques for reducing the number of parameters, which could fall under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on image classification and object detection tasks, which could fall under the scope of multimedia (cs.MM).
